-- Canaccord Hires Richards, Merrill Lynch Adds King, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-08-02T16:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-02/canaccord-hires-richards-merrill-lynch-adds-king-vlaad-says.html
Canaccord Genuity, the  capital
markets  unit of Canaccord Financial Inc., hired Geoffrey Richards as managing director and head of U.S. special
situations and restructuring in New York from William Blair &
Co., according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  *  RBC Capital Markets  in New York added Jonathan Tretler from
Deutsche Bank, as  investment banking  managing director with the
consumer retail group focusing on food and beverages. Noel Brown, from Piper Jaffray, joined RBC as health-care managing
director in investment banking.  * Bank of America Merrill Lynch hired Gabriella King as managing
director, global corporate banking from HSBC, where she was head
of Canadian financial institutions.  * Tom Liston, former director of Canadian research and
technology research analyst at  Cantor Fitzgerald , joined
Difference Capital Financial Inc. as managing partner.  * Clarke Markle joined Vantage Asset Management as the director
of operations having just completed his MBA.  * Another MBA grad, Alex Watt, is at Byron Capital Markets as a
research associate.  * Borealis Infrastructure hired Simon Forsyth as an associate
from  Capstone Infrastructure Corp. (CSE)   * DNA Capital in Montreal added In Sunwoo as an associate.
Sunwoo was previously at BMO Capital Markets as an investment
and corporate banking analyst.  * BMO Capital Markets hired Daniel Cerulli as an analyst from
Roynat Capital, where he was a private equity analyst.  To contact the reporter on this story:
